<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-25T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">550.AD1/319a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-26T00:00:00-04:00">April 26,
                                1943—midnight.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>803. For Murphy. Your 679, April 22.<note n="33" xml:id="d751fn33">Not
                            printed.</note> On the understanding that a delegation will be named
                        jointly by the High Command and <pb facs="0849" n="839" xml:id="pg_839"/>
                        the National Committee, you are authorized to extend formally to the
                        appropriate French authorities the invitation quoted in the Department’s
                        712, April 14.<note n="35" xml:id="d751fn35">See telegram No. 2384, April
                            14, midnight, to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom, <ref target="#pg_837">p. 837</ref>.</note> It is, of course, understood
                        that the French representatives will participate in the food conference with
                        the same status as representatives of other countries.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>